Hence > 8 or 9 places. What does your maths say about 10 decimals?
Absolutely. Any RTK grade steering system should be using as many decimals as possible up to that point. It’s just past that your adding noise.

If they are measuring using more than 8 or 9 decimal places they aren’t really adding more accuracy. At that point you are measuring at an atom-like level. Not much GPS gear can measure that, or steering systems drive to it.
